Hi there, newby Debian user and trying to adjust my monitor properly.  I
am able to run "sudo ddccontrol -p" and it finds my monitor, but if I
then return to my desktop and run gddccontrol it displays the message:

        No monitor supporting DDC/CI available
        
        If your graphics card need it, please check all the required
        kernel modules are loaded (i2c-dev, and your framebuffer
        driver).

Now, I didn't load the framebuffer driver because the doc recommends
using direct PCI memory access with Radeon cards.  I am running a Radeon
9800 Pro.  I have the etch distro of Debian.

The docs say that to use direct PCI memory access I don't have to do
anything special so how come I can't use the GUI gddccontrol?

Thanks for any help, and remember I'm new to this linux thing so please
go into painful detail on any steps I might need to do.

Jeff





