The output of this command would be helpful:

LANG=3D LC_ALL=3D ddccontrol -p -c -d

Be sure to run it as root or with sudo.  Also, be sure and include the
make/model/etc info about your monitor.

> So now that I can launch the GUI / gddccontrol manually through
> terminal, how can I get it to retain my settings and implement them each
> time I login?.  Is there a way for it to run properly when I select it
> from the Gnome menu?
>=20

You will have to change the device permissions, as described here:
http://ddccontrol.sourceforge.net/doc/0.4/ch02s04.html

Regards,

-Roberto
